Colombia Stocks: Coltejer, Pacific Rubiales, Textiles Fabricato

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-04-06T20:29:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/colombia-stocks-coltejer-pacific-rubiales-textiles-fabricato.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index gained 0.2 percent to 14,632.93, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.2 percent to 1,719.57.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp (PREC)   climbed 1.7 percent
to 54,700 pesos, the highest level since March 11. The Toronto-
based  oil company  with fields in  Colombia  said it plans to buy
back as much as 11.6 million of its common shares, according to
a regulatory filing.  Exporters rose after Colombia agreed to rework  labor laws 
and crack down on violence against union organizers in a deal
with the Obama administration that clears the way for a free-
trade agreement to be considered by Congress.  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)  , the Medellin-
based textile producer, surged 5.9 percent to 45.2 pesos, the
highest level since September 2007.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)   rose 1.2 percent to 86 centavos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
